{
  "texts": [
    "After considering and rejecting several potential criteria, I will suggestin Sect.",
    "\"The indifference criterion\"-that the indifference criterion is most appropriate to conceptualise manipulation.",
    "Manipulation is a form of influence (Coons & Weber, 2014b).",
    "As social animals, humans influence each other in countless ways.",
    "Some influences are intentional, such as a speech act, while others are unintentional, such as the intimidating effect a very tall person may have on others."
  ]
}